com.link_intersystems.lang.reflect.criteria

Class ElementCriteria<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.link_intersystems.lang.reflect.criteria.ElementCriteria<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ClassCriteria, MemberCriteria

    public abstract class ElementCriteria<T>
extends Object
implements Cloneable
    An ElementCriteria provides selection, and filtering capabilities for member based criteria. AllElementCriterias provide methods to obtain an Iterable. After the Iterable is constructed it ensures that all Iterators it constructs apply the same iteration rules. These are the rules of the critera at construction time of the Iterable. This rule is ensured for properties of the criteria. It can not be ensured for properties of dependent objects, e.g. for Predicates that have state like a unique predicate and are added using add(Predicate). 

     ClassCriteria criteria = new ClassCriteria();
 criteria.setTraverseOrder(TraverseOrder.INTERFACES_FIRST);
 Iterator<Class<?>> classIterator = criteria.getIterable(ArrayList.class)
                .iterator();
 /*
  * Should not have an effect on the iterator or iterable created before
  */
 criteria.setTraverseOrder(TraverseOrder.SUPERCLASS_ONLY);
 criteria.add(new AssignablePredicate(AbstractList.class));
 criteria.setResultSelection(Selection.LAST);

 Iterator<Class<?>> secondIterator = criteria.getIterable(ArrayList.class)
                .iterator();

      • add

        public void add(Predicate<T> predicate)
        Use the defined predicate as a filter when searching for elements. Multiple calls to this method will combine the predicates with a logical 'and' operator. The type of objects that the Predicate must be able to handle is defined by subclasses.
        Parameters:
        predicate - the predicate to use when filtering elements.
        Since:
        1.0.0;

      • applyElementFilter

        protected Iterator<T> applyElementFilter(Iterator<T> iterator)
        Takes the iterator and wraps it into a filtering iterator that applies the Predicates that were configured via add(Predicate).
        Parameters:
        iterator - the iterator that the filter should be applied on.
        Returns:
        an Iterator that filters the elements of the given Iterator according to the filter Predicates defined by add(Predicate).
        Since:
        1.0.0;
